                <head>33. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>French Ambassador Alphand met with Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RD1"
                        >Rusk</persName> on February 20, 1961, to discuss the situation in the
                    Congo. According to a memorandum of the conversation, “Alphand said he thought
                    we should be very tough with the Soviets and tell them frankly we would not
                    accept a Communist regime in the Congo. He added <persName corresp="#p_KNS1"
                        >Khrushchev</persName> anyway is not in a good logistic position vis-à-vis
                    the Congo. The Secretary agreed and said that sometimes he thought we were over
                    pessimistic about our own position in the Congo since the Soviets were having
                    troubles too.” For text of the memorandum of conversation, see <ref
                        target="frus1961-63v20#pg_70">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1961–1963, volume XX, pages
                        70</ref>–<ref target="frus1961-63v20#pg_73">73</ref>.</p>
            </div>
